# The Market

## What Exists Today

| Company | What They Do | Gap They Leave |
|---|---|---|
| Recykal (Hyderabad, $83M raised) | EPR marketplace — connects brands with recyclers | Does NOT give recyclers operational tools |
| ScrapQ | Consumer scrap pickup app | Consumer-facing only, not B2B operations |
| Kabadiwala Connect | Consumer pickup service | No recycler tools |
| The Kabadiwala | Consumer pickup + awareness | No B2B platform |
| Waste Ventures | Waste collection management | Focused on municipal waste, not recycling ops |

## What's Missing — The Recycler's Daily Life Today

| Task | How They Do It Today | What They Need |
|---|---|---|
| Track incoming material (weight, type, source, price) | Paper register + WhatsApp photos | Digital weighing integration + material database |
| Track processing output and recovery rates | Mental math or no tracking at all | Dashboard showing input vs output per material |
| Generate SPCB/CPCB compliance reports | Hire CA or consultant every quarter | Auto-generated reports from daily data |
| Issue EPR disposal certificates | Manual Word documents | Digital certificate generation with QR verification |
| Track scrap prices across cities | Calling 5-10 dealers every morning | Real-time price feed like MCX but for scrap |
| Manage buyers and sellers | Phone contacts + memory | Simple CRM with deal history |
| Generate GST invoices for scrap sales | Tally or manual bills | Built-in invoicing tied to material records |
| Know profitability per material type | No idea — they guess | Automatic P&L per metal type |
| Manage workers and shifts | WhatsApp group | Simple attendance + task assignment |
| Store regulatory documents (licenses, consents) | Physical files that get lost | Digital document vault with expiry alerts |

**The recycler has 10 daily pain points and ZERO good software solutions.** Every other industry got its "Zoho" or "Freshworks" years ago. Recycling is still in the dark ages.

## Market Size

| Segment | Number in India | Software Willingness | Revenue Potential |
|---|---|---|---|
| Authorized e-waste recyclers | 500+ registered | High — regulation forces digitization | ₹5,000-20,000/month per recycler |
| Authorized e-waste dismantlers | 1,200+ registered | High | ₹3,000-10,000/month |
| Plastic recyclers | 10,000+ | Medium — growing with EPR | ₹2,000-8,000/month |
| Metal scrap dealers (medium-large) | 50,000+ | Low-Medium — but growing | ₹1,000-5,000/month |
| Paper recyclers | 5,000+ | Medium | ₹2,000-5,000/month |
| PROs (Producer Responsibility Organizations) | 50+ | Very High — their entire business is compliance | ₹20,000-1,00,000/month |
| Brands (EPR compliance teams) | 500+ | Very High | ₹50,000-5,00,000/month |

**Conservative estimate:** If you capture 5% of authorized recyclers and dismantlers (85 customers) at ₹8,000/month average = ₹6.8L/month MRR in Year 2-3 alone. That's before marketplace or data revenue.

