# Phase 2: Industry Research

```
⏱  Month 4-12 (overlaps with Phase 1) · 🎯 Understand the industry deeply
💰 Cost: ₹0-5,000 (just your time + travel to scrap markets)
```

> **You are not becoming a scrap trader. You are becoming the person who
> UNDERSTANDS scrap traders better than any software developer in India.**
> This understanding is your product's foundation.

## Month 4-6: Visit and Observe (While Still at Current Job)

| Week | Action | What You Learn |
|---|---|---|
| Week 1 | Visit Hyderabad's scrap markets (Afzalgunj, Falaknuma) on a Saturday | How the physical market works — scale, flow, chaos |
| Week 2 | Talk to 5 medium-size scrap dealers. Ask about their daily operations. | Pain points, how they track material, pricing, invoicing |
| Week 3 | Visit 2 authorized e-waste recyclers in Hyderabad (find on CPCB website) | How recyclers process, what records they keep, compliance burden |
| Week 4 | Search LinkedIn for "recycling" or "e-waste" + "Hyderabad". Connect with 10 people. | Industry network — these become your future beta users |
| Week 5 | Attend any waste management event in Hyderabad (T-Hub hosts sustainability events) | Industry language, trends, who the key players are |
| Week 6 | Visit Recykal's office (they're in Gachibowli — request an informal chat) | What the market leader does and DOESN'T do |
| Week 7-8 | Compile your findings. Write down every pain point you heard. | Your product requirements doc — straight from the user's mouth |

## Month 7-9: Deep Dive Interviews (After Landing US Remote Job — Evenings Free)

| Action | How | Target |
|---|---|---|
| Interview 20 recyclers about their daily workflow | Visit in person + phone calls | Understand: What takes the most time? What causes errors? What regulations confuse them? |
| Interview 5 PROs (Producer Responsibility Organizations) | LinkedIn + phone | Understand: How do they track collection? What data do they need from recyclers? |
| Interview 3 SPCB officials (if possible) | Visit TSPCB office, ask about digital compliance | Understand: What reporting format do they want? What's changing in regulations? |
| Study Recykal, ScrapQ, Kabadiwala Connect products | Sign up, use their apps, read their reviews | Understand: What they do well, what users complain about, where gaps are |
| Read E-Waste Management Rules 2022 completely | CPCB website (free PDF) | Understand: What data must be tracked by law — this becomes your mandatory feature set |

## Month 10-12: Define Your Product

By now you've talked to 30+ industry people. You know their pain points better than they can articulate. You write a product spec.

**Your product (working name: "RecycleOS" or "CircularDesk"):**

A simple web + mobile app that a recycler opens every morning and uses all day to run their operations. Think of it as "Zoho for Recyclers" but much simpler.

**Core features (MVP — build ONLY these first):**

| Feature | What It Does | Why They Need It | Tech Stack |
|---|---|---|---|
| Material Intake Log | Record: date, source, material type, weight, price paid, photo | Currently in paper register — gets lost, no analysis possible | React form + Supabase DB + phone camera |
| Output Tracking | Record: what went in, what came out, recovery percentage | They have NO IDEA of their actual recovery rates | React dashboard + charts (Recharts) |
| Daily Price Tracker | Show today's scrap prices for copper, aluminum, brass, steel, e-waste grades in 5 cities | Currently they call 5-10 people every morning — wastes 1 hour | Web scraping + manual input + API |
| Compliance Document Vault | Upload and store SPCB consent, CPCB registration, EPR certificates with expiry alerts | Physical files get lost. Expiry dates are missed. | File upload + date-based notifications |
| Basic Invoice Generator | Generate GST invoice for scrap sales from material records | Currently using Tally or handwritten bills | PDF generation from transaction data |
| Simple Dashboard | Today's intake, output, pending sales, cash flow | They have ZERO visibility into their own business | React dashboard with summary cards |

**What you DON'T build in MVP:** Marketplace, AI features, complex analytics, mobile-first (web is fine for MVP), multi-location, team management. These come in Phase 5.

