## Getting Beta Users (From Phase 2 Relationships)

You already talked to 20+ recyclers in Phase 2. Go back to the 5-10 who were most vocal about their problems.

| Step | What You Say | Expected Response |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | "Remember when you told me tracking material intake is a headache? I built a simple tool for that. Can I show you in 10 minutes?" | "Yes, show me" (most will say yes — you're not selling, you're showing) |
| 2 | Show the app on your phone. Let THEM enter one material record. | They'll either say "oh this is actually good" or they'll point out what's wrong/missing |
| 3 | "Use it free for 2 months. Just give me honest feedback every week on WhatsApp." | 5-10 will say yes (it's free and you're helping them) |
| 4 | After 2 months, ask: "Would you pay ₹2,000/month for this?" | 3-5 will say yes if the product genuinely helped them |

**The MOST IMPORTANT rule of beta testing:** Sit NEXT to the recycler while they use your app for the first time. Watch their fingers. Watch their face. Every confusion, every pause, every wrong tap is a bug YOU need to fix. Don't ask "do you like it?" — watch what they DO.

